
[1]extenuation

   EXTENUA'TION, n. The act of making thin; the process of growing thin or
   lean; the losing of flesh.

   1. The act representing any thing less wrong, faulty or criminal than
   it is in fact; palliation; opposed to aggravation; as the extenuation
   of faults, injuries or crimes.

   2. Mitigation; alleviation; as the extenuation of punishment.

                                [Not common.]
